'''Preeti Singh''' (born 26 October 1971) is an Indian author<ref>[http://epaper.tribuneindia.com/258981/Life-Style/LS_18_April_2014#page/2/2 "Torn between commitment and desire"], ''[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]'', 18 April 2014
*[http://epaper.indianexpress.com/259807/Chandigarh/19-April-2014#page/27/3 "The Road Less Travelled"], ''[[The Indian Express]]'', 19 April 2014</ref> based at [[Chandigarh]]. Singh has been working as a professional writer since last 15 years before authoring her two best-selling novels. Her [[debut novel]] - ''[[Flirting with Fate (novel)|Flirting With Fate]]''<ref>[http://epaper.tribuneindia.com/258981/Life-Style/LS_18_April_2014#page/2/2 "Torn between commitment and desire"], ''The Tribune'', 18 April 2014</ref> was published by Mahaveer Publishers, India in 2012, followed by ''Crossroads'', which was published by Authors Press, India, in 2014. Her second and latest book ''Crossroads'' has made its place in the ''India Book Of Records'' as the First Indian Fiction having real-life people as characters.

On 17 December 2015, she was felicitated with the ''Swayamsiddha Award'' for [[Self-made woman|self-made women]] who have been self achievers in their fields, by the Anupama Foundation, [[Lucknow]].<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://epaper.jagran.com/ePaperArticle/18-dec-2015-edition-Lucknow-page_28-15604-11258-11.htm
|title=स्वयंसिद्धा अवॉर्ड विभूतियाँ सम्मानित
|date= 18 December 2015
|work=[[Dainik Jagran]]
}}</ref> Her third crime thriller novel ''Watched'', published by Omji Publishing House, released in October 2016.<ref name="TI">{{cite news|title=You are being ‘watched’|url=http://www.tribuneindia.com/news/life-style/gyan-zone/you-are-being-watched/330471.html|publisher=[[Tribune India]]|date=1 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=क्राइम से बचने के लिए अपने आसपास नजर रखें|url=http://www.jagran.com/punjab/chandigarh-14917810.html|date=23 October 2016|publisher=[[Jagran]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=सस्पेंस से भरपूर क्राइम थिलर वॉच्ड: प्रीति|url=http://dainiksaveratimes.epapr.in/c/15075264|date=23 October 2016|publisher=Dainik Savera}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=क्राइमथ्रिलर वॉच्ड रिलीज़|url=http://epaper.punjabkesari.in/978533/punjab-kesari-chandigarh-kesari/Chandigarh-kesari#page/5/2|date=24 October 2016|publisher=[[Punjab Kesari]]}}</ref>

==Biography==
Singh belongs to an army family. Her father [[Major General]] [[Kulwant Singh (general)|Kulwant Singh]]<ref>[http://www.invinciblemilitary.org/about/Maj_Gen_Singh.html Major General Kulwant Singh]</ref> retired from the Indian Army and her late mother, Sonya Kulwant Singh died due to lung cancer. Though she is an epileptic since birth, Singh grew with an urge to overcome her handicap someday, which she successfully did with the launch of her debut novel. Singh completed her schooling from [[La Martiniere Lucknow|La Martiniere School, Lucknow]]. She then graduated from MCM DAV College For Women, Chandigarh with an English honours and pursued her master's degree in English literature from [[Panjab University, Chandigarh|Punjab University,Chandigarh]]. Singh acquired a Post Graduation Diploma in Journalism and Mass Communication from [[IGNOU|IGNOU, Delhi]] and began her career as an editor with [[Amity University, Noida]]. After completing her B.Ed. (Bachelor of Education) from [[Annamalai University]], she began teaching in army schools all over India before joining an SEO Company as a creative content writer. She is now settled in Chandigarh with her family and freelances as an editor for a wide clientele, globally, via her official website.<ref>[http://epaper.indianexpress.com/259807/Chandigarh/19-April-2014#page/27/3 "The Road Less Travelled"], ''[[The Indian Express]]'', 19 April 2014</ref><ref>[http://epaper.dailypostindia.com/Details.aspx?id=100176&boxid=57372&uid=&dat=2014-04-17 "Strong Enough To Fight Alone"], ''[[Daily Post India]]'', 17 April 2014</ref>

In April 2019, Preeti Singh and her epileptic dog named Sizzler Singh were interviewed by [[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]] on how dogs can sense and warn family members just before an [[epileptic seizure]] is about to happen.<ref>{{cite news |title=Man's Best Friend, forever |url=https://epaper.tribuneindia.com/2094553/Life+Style-(Chd)/LS-02-April-2019#page/1/2 |publisher=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)]] |date=2 April 2019}}</ref>
==Works==
Singh debuted with a crime thriller [[Flirting with Fate (novel)|''Flirting With Fate'']]<ref>[http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Chandigarh/Thriller-Debut/SP-Article1-889404.aspx "Thriller Debut", ''[[Hindustan Times]]'', 15 July 2012] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140130064125/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Chandigarh/Thriller-Debut/SP-Article1-889404.aspx |date=30 January 2014 }}</ref> released by Mahaveer Publishers in 2012.  The book was nominated for the Commonwealth Booker's Prize of 2012 and was also awarded the Best Debut Crime Fiction of 2012<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://m.amarujala.com/chandigarh/photo-gallery/city-events-chandigarh-2/?page=2
|title=City Events @ Chandigarh
|date=
|work=[[Amar Ujala]]
|language=Hindi}}</ref><ref>[http://www.satyaswadesh.com/Epaper/2014/04/17/pages/High/18.jpg "क्रॉसरोअड्स हर नारी की कहानी", ''Satya Sandesh'', 17 April 2014]</ref><ref>[http://epaper.amarujala.com//svww_zoomart.php?Artname=20140417i_006121004&ileft=359&itop=466&zoomRatio=156&AN=20140417i_006121004 "किताब ऐसी", ''[[Amar Ujala]]'' , April १७, २०१४]</ref> ''Crossroads'' is an attempt at tapping the emotional aspect of women undergoing domestic abuse and suffering. The book is unique as it holds real-life people with real names, from various cities, as the main characters.<ref>{{cite news|title=भारतीय नारी की मनोस्थिति का चिट्ठा 'क्रॉसरोड्स'|url=http://www.jagran.com/punjab/chandigarh-11239157.html|publisher=[[Jagran]]|date=16 April 2014}}</ref>

Singh is a core member of ''Helping Souls'', a [[Panchkula]]-based [[Non-governmental organization|NGO]], working towards making animal shelters as well as improving the living standards of slum women and children.<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://epaper.amarujala.com/pk/my/20151226/07.html?format=pdf
|title=हेलपिंग सोल्स एनजीओ की ओर से कार्यक्रम का आयोजन
|date=26 December 2015
|work=[[Amar Ujala]]
|language=Hindi}}</ref>

Her third crime thriller novel ''Watched'' released in October 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=लेखिका प्रीति सिंह की क्राइमथ्रिलर बुक "वॉच्ड" का विमोचन|url=http://epaper.aajsamaaj.com/indexaajsamaj.php?pagedate=2016-10-24&edcode=77&subcode=77&mod=1&pgnum=2|date=24 December 2016|publisher=AAj Samaaj}}</ref><ref name="TI" /><ref name="DB" />

==Awards and recognition==
* Nominated for the Commonwealth Booker's Prize 2012 and also Awarded the Best Debut Crime Fiction Novel of 2012
* Featured in the Coffee Table Book Of Leading Personalities of Chandigarh released by Aneesh Bhanot<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/A-coffee-table-book-to-honour-City-Beautiful/articleshow/9093164.cms
|title=A coffee table book to honour City Beautiful
|date= 4 Jul 2011
|work=[[Times of India]]
}}</ref>
* Her novel ''Crossroads'' has made its place in the India Book Of Records as the First Indian Fiction having real life people as characters.
* She was felicitated with the ''Swayamsiddha Award'' for [[Self-made woman|self made women]] who have been [[:wikt:achievement|self achievers]] in their fields, by the Anupama Foundation, [[Lucknow]], on 17 December 2015.<ref>{{cite news
|url=http://epaper.amarujala.com/lc/my/20151218/04.html?format=im
|title=योगदान के लिए सम्मानित हुई महिलाएं
|date= 18 December 2015
|work=[[Amar Ujala]]
}}</ref>
* She has been given the Best Author Award 2016 for ''Sanmati Literary Awards 2016'' for her novel Crossroads by Pawan Jain and The Aagman Family in [[Delhi]].<ref name="DB">{{cite news|title=क्राइमथ्रिलर ‘वॉच्ड’ की मुख्य पात्र किंजल जोशी|url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/UT-CHD-HMU-NES-MAT-latest-chandigarh-news-020502-1275355-NOR.html|date=29 October 2016|publisher=[[Daily Bhaskar]]}}</ref>
* Singh was facilitated with the ''Bharat Nirman Literary Excellence Award'' 2017 for Writing at the 5th Asiad Literature Festival on 17 September 2017 in the Press Club Chandigarh.<ref>{{cite news|title=Fifth Asiad Literature Festival and Defence Lit organised in Chandigarh Press Club|url=http://www.face2news.com/news/32177-fifith-asiad-literature-festival-in-chandigarh-press-club-.aspx|publisher=Face2News.com|date=September 17, 2017}}</ref>
* Preeti Singh was invited as one of the eminent speakers amongst other dignitaries like [[Shabana Azmi]] and [[Kalki Subramaniam]] at the ''Women Leadership Conclave'' hosted by FMRT, [[New Delhi]] on 30 September 2018.<ref>{{cite news |title=FMRT provides platform to women with difference |url=http://www.fab-info.com/fmrt-provides-platform-to-women-with-difference/ |publisher=fab-info.com |date=September 26, 2018}}</ref>

